## Beringia Marine Migration Rules

- Treat `apps/web` as the active web app surface; do not add new root-level web code in `src/` or `lib/`.
- Keep newsletter flow patterns intact unless explicitly asked to remove them.
- Use one canonical source for Insights content and consume it from both `/insights` and `/insights/:slug`.
- Avoid duplicate article registries, duplicated fetch logic, or hardcoded insight route strings.
- Prefer shared helpers for insight URLs and SEO image resolution.
- Keep Insights structured data aligned with route slugs and canonical URLs.
- Use `updatedAt` and reading-time fields when available for article metadata and JSON-LD.
- Maintain a staged migration approach: keep currently-required web-side Sanity runtime code until a dedicated migration pass is requested.
- Remove legacy Vital Ice branding/assets when encountered; replace with neutral Beringia usage.
- After edits, run lint/type checks scoped to changed areas and avoid unrelated refactors.
